<% provide(:title, 'Add New Item') %>
<h1>Add a New Item to Trade</h1>

<div class="row">
  <div class="span6 offset1">
    <%= simple_form_for(@possession) do |f| %>
      <%= f.input :name %>
      <%= f.input :description %>
      <%= f.input :value %>
      <%= f.submit "Add Item", class: "btn btn-large btn-primary" %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <div class="column">
  	<h2>Tips!</h2>
    <ul>
    <li>Try to give your item a descriptive title.  That is how people will find it</li>  
    <li>Accurately describe the condition of your item to insure that whoever gets your item gets what they expect</li>
    <li>The value you set is visible only by you.  We use it to make sure you don't accidentally trade a TV for a lamp (unless you value the lamp more).</li>
  </div>
</div>
